WEBVTT

00:03.771 --> 00:06.407
Yeah!
[ Cheering ]

00:06.440 --> 00:08.142
Hey, there you are!

00:08.176 --> 00:11.011
Wanted you to be here
for the inaugural run

00:11.045 --> 00:12.880
of the Stew-Chew train.

00:14.215 --> 00:16.150
You know, if I was
still a partner,

00:16.184 --> 00:17.985
I would say
this is totally stupid,

00:18.018 --> 00:19.987
but as
a part-time employee,

00:20.020 --> 00:22.423
I'll still say it's stupid,
but you won't have to listen.

00:22.456 --> 00:24.225
You don't get it.

00:24.258 --> 00:25.559
There's a lot of bars

00:25.593 --> 00:27.395
where people can
watch the Bears play.

00:27.428 --> 00:31.199
We have got to have
a gimmick to stand out,

00:31.232 --> 00:34.735
and everybody loves those
sushi conveyor-belt places.

00:34.768 --> 00:36.937
You mean the places where
you sit and watch the sushi

00:36.970 --> 00:39.440
go round and round
until it becomes poisonous?

00:39.473 --> 00:40.574
Ugh!

00:40.608 --> 00:42.410
Okay, everybody!
Get out your phones.

00:42.443 --> 00:44.912
You're about to witness
stew history!

00:44.945 --> 00:46.180
[ Train whistle blows ]

00:46.214 --> 00:49.117
[ Laughing hysterically ]

00:51.385 --> 00:52.486
[ Gasps ]

00:55.256 --> 00:56.790
Hey,
is my order ready yet?

00:56.824 --> 00:58.359
And if it is,
could you please hand it to me,

00:58.392 --> 01:00.894
as opposed to shooting it at me
with a train?

01:00.928 --> 01:03.464
Oh, looks to me like

01:03.497 --> 01:05.133
that little engineer's
been drinking.

01:05.999 --> 01:07.401
And at that size,
it only takes them

01:07.435 --> 01:09.737
a thimble of alcohol
to impair their judgment.

01:11.172 --> 01:13.607
What are you doing here?
Are you following me?

01:13.641 --> 01:15.209
No,
I'm just getting lunch.

01:15.243 --> 01:17.111
But I know you're moving
into Aldo's soon,

01:17.145 --> 01:19.280
and I would like
to spend some time together.

01:19.313 --> 01:20.748
Is it okay
if I sit with you?

01:20.781 --> 01:22.983
I guess I'm the bad guy
if I say no.

01:23.016 --> 01:24.518
Let's find out. No.

01:25.619 --> 01:27.988
Come on.
I'm gonna miss you.

01:28.021 --> 01:31.159
And I swear, I am done
trying to control your life.

01:31.192 --> 01:33.227
Except for this one,
last thing.

01:33.261 --> 01:34.628
You forgot your
birth control pills

01:34.662 --> 01:35.929
at the house
this morning.

01:35.963 --> 01:37.665
Okay, so that's why
you're here.

01:37.698 --> 01:39.633
Why are you going
through my stuff?

01:39.667 --> 01:41.335
I was looking to see
if you had any weed,

01:41.369 --> 01:43.804
which I also found,
and that's really why I'm here.

01:43.837 --> 01:45.739
I'm starving.

01:45.773 --> 01:47.641
Okay,
I didn't forget them.

01:47.675 --> 01:50.144
I'm just taking a break
because they make me moody.

01:50.178 --> 01:51.812
Have you been taking them
since you were 10?

01:51.845 --> 01:54.047
'Cause I'm pretty sure
that's a pre-existing condition.

01:55.216 --> 01:58.018
Anyway, I really hope
you and Aldo aren't having sex.

01:58.051 --> 02:01.021
Oh, we're having sex --
tons of it.

02:01.054 --> 02:03.824
-Yeah!
-Whoo!

02:03.857 --> 02:06.126
That was a really
unfortunate coincidence.

02:06.727 --> 02:08.462
Have you ever noticed
that every time

02:08.496 --> 02:10.097
someone tries to push me
in one direction,

02:10.130 --> 02:11.299
I go the other way?

02:11.332 --> 02:12.866
Well, watch this.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.034
I'm done taking
these pills.

02:14.067 --> 02:15.269
Have fun worrying.

02:15.303 --> 02:20.441
**

02:20.474 --> 02:27.481
**

02:28.249 --> 02:35.256
**

02:36.089 --> 02:43.096
**

02:43.997 --> 02:51.004
**

02:54.375 --> 02:57.411
Hey, Louise, I just got a tweet
that your band's going on tour.

02:57.445 --> 02:59.547
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:59.580 --> 03:02.015
We're gonna do a few weeks
in Memphis and Nashville.

03:02.049 --> 03:05.018
I love those cities,
and I didn't want to miss it.

03:05.052 --> 03:07.154
Even though
it's gonna be hard

03:07.187 --> 03:09.757
being away from my new hubby
for so long.

03:09.790 --> 03:12.926
-Oh.
-Oh, isn't that romantic?

03:12.960 --> 03:15.563
Baby,
you're the greatest.

03:15.596 --> 03:18.532
I wouldn't want to be away
from me for that long, either.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.368
You know, and since
I'm gonna be moving in here,

03:20.401 --> 03:24.071
I thought I would rent out
my condo before I go.

03:24.104 --> 03:26.340
I mean, what's the point
in having it sit there empty

03:26.374 --> 03:28.376
when I can bring in
some extra cash?

03:28.409 --> 03:30.944
I love you!

03:30.978 --> 03:34.282
And I love you even more
when you come with extra cash.

03:34.315 --> 03:37.017
-Ooh, so beautiful.
-Ooh, cash.

03:37.050 --> 03:39.920
So greedy.

03:39.953 --> 03:42.390
So, then, it's okay if
I bring my furniture here?

03:42.423 --> 03:45.058
I don't want a bunch
of strangers messing it up.

03:45.092 --> 03:47.194
You're afraid of renters
wrecking your stuff,

03:47.227 --> 03:49.196
so you're bringing it
to the hillbilly frat house?

03:49.229 --> 03:51.932
Hey, we know how to take care
of valuable things.

03:51.965 --> 03:53.066
Are they valuable?

03:53.100 --> 03:54.234
[ Chuckles ]

03:54.268 --> 03:55.769
I thought I raised you
better than that.

03:55.803 --> 03:59.139
Now she'll never believe
her things were stolen.

04:03.110 --> 04:05.145
Can I help you?
Uh, yeah.

04:05.178 --> 04:06.780
Is, uh, River around?

04:06.814 --> 04:08.482
I want to talk to him
about a book he gave me.

04:08.516 --> 04:10.484
River's on
a silent retreat.

04:10.518 --> 04:11.652
Oh.
I'm Nick.

04:11.685 --> 04:13.787
I'm the real brains
behind the operation.

04:13.821 --> 04:15.055
I restock the books.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.056
I light the incense
every morning.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.158
It is natural to be intimidated,
but don't be.

04:18.191 --> 04:20.561
[ Laughs ]
Okay, I'll try.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.463
I'm Darlene.
Hi.

04:22.496 --> 04:26.066
River was kinda helping me
with some problems.

04:26.099 --> 04:28.068
Hmm.
Have you read
the "Dao De Jing"?

04:28.101 --> 04:29.169
Oh, sure.

04:29.202 --> 04:30.738
Yeah, there's a lot
of practical advice in there,

04:30.771 --> 04:31.739
and then
there's some stuff

04:31.772 --> 04:33.841
that's just ephemeral
and esoteric.

04:33.874 --> 04:36.009
Okay, so,
it's not just me.

04:36.043 --> 04:38.078
I'm looking for a better way
to live my life,

04:38.111 --> 04:40.348
but good God, throw in
a picture once in a while.

04:40.381 --> 04:42.316
[ Laughs ] I know.

04:42.350 --> 04:44.618
Sometimes, Eastern wisdom can be
up its own butt a little.

04:44.652 --> 04:47.154
It wouldn't hurt
to lighten it up, right?
Yeah, yeah.

04:47.187 --> 04:50.123
There's a reason Confucius made
all those jokes, right?

04:50.157 --> 04:51.291
Confucius did not
make jokes.

04:51.325 --> 04:53.026
Th-That was
just white people

04:53.060 --> 04:54.762
making fun
of Eastern religion.

04:54.795 --> 04:56.964
Huh. White people
making fun of something

04:56.997 --> 04:57.965
they don't understand.

04:57.998 --> 04:59.299
Didn't see that one
coming.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.134
[ Chuckles ]

05:01.168 --> 05:03.136
I'm just -- I'm just having
a really hard time

05:03.170 --> 05:05.138
with the whole
Dao "not-doing" thing.

05:05.172 --> 05:07.140
Hmm.
Mind if I sit?

05:07.174 --> 05:09.109
I'm not paying your salary.
Go ahead.

05:09.142 --> 05:11.044
S-So,
I know I'm not River,

05:11.078 --> 05:13.113
but I think
maybe I can help.

05:13.146 --> 05:14.715
Um...

05:14.748 --> 05:17.551
I know how hard
the not-doing thing is.

05:17.585 --> 05:20.320
When I was a stockbroker,
I was a doer, too.

05:20.354 --> 05:22.055
I was doing coke.
I was doing speed.

05:22.089 --> 05:24.358
I was doing online poker
with my clients' money.

05:24.392 --> 05:27.194
Wow, you win
the "doer" contest.

05:27.227 --> 05:28.896
[ Laughs ]

05:28.929 --> 05:30.964
And you were able
to actually quit all that

05:30.998 --> 05:33.367
by just embracing
Eastern philosophy?

05:33.401 --> 05:34.502
Not exactly.

05:34.535 --> 05:35.969
I quit doing drugs
the second they fired me

05:36.003 --> 05:37.571
for being
a drug addict.

05:37.605 --> 05:39.640
And that's what forced me
to -- to look for answers,

05:39.673 --> 05:41.642
and I found them here --
which was a blessing,

05:41.675 --> 05:44.011
'cause I really like
my life now.

05:44.044 --> 05:47.080
I'd like to like
my life.

05:47.114 --> 05:49.717
So, is there anything else
in this place

05:49.750 --> 05:51.184
that I should be studying?

05:51.218 --> 05:55.022
I guess the best one for me
was the teachings of Buddha.

05:55.055 --> 05:57.725
It led me to a greater sense
of acceptance.

05:57.758 --> 06:00.193
Okay, yeah, yeah.
I'm not a big acceptor.

06:00.227 --> 06:03.030
More of an "exert my will
until everybody resents me"

06:03.063 --> 06:04.231
kind of girl.

06:04.264 --> 06:05.433
That's my weakness.

06:05.466 --> 06:07.000
I love a woman
who can make me resent her.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.101
[ Chuckles ]

06:08.135 --> 06:09.537
Here you are.

06:09.570 --> 06:11.104
One matcha latte
with oat milk.
Oh.

06:11.138 --> 06:13.373
Ah, thank you.
Hey, I didn't know
you were working today.

06:13.407 --> 06:15.108
I missed you. Hi.

06:15.142 --> 06:17.077
Oh, man.
I don't get hugs at work.

06:17.110 --> 06:19.513
Just pat-downs when they think
we're stealing office supplies.

06:19.547 --> 06:22.182
I don't even need the envelopes.
It's just like a game to me now.

06:22.215 --> 06:25.085
[ Laughs ] Darlene,
this is my daughter, Brook.

06:25.118 --> 06:27.120
It's a pleasure
to meet you.

06:27.154 --> 06:28.456
Dad,
I'm sorry to interrupt,

06:28.489 --> 06:30.090
but I need to talk to you
about something.

06:30.123 --> 06:32.192
Oh.
Oh, if you want,
I can step away for a second.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.595
Oh, no,
it's not a big deal.

06:34.628 --> 06:37.030
I'm going camping tomorrow
with my friends.
Uh-huh.

06:37.064 --> 06:39.933
Do you think it's a bad idea
to try mushrooms?

06:39.967 --> 06:42.402
[ Laughs ] I'm sorry.

06:43.671 --> 06:45.739
I'm sorry to pry.
I got to hear this.

06:45.773 --> 06:47.741
What does Buddha say
about your teenage daughter

06:47.775 --> 06:49.209
tripping balls
with her friends?

06:49.242 --> 06:50.944
[ Chuckles ]
Well, Buddha says

06:50.978 --> 06:53.280
regardless of what
a parent wants,

06:53.313 --> 06:55.415
a child will be true
to their nature.

06:55.449 --> 06:56.984
What's your gut
telling you?

06:57.017 --> 06:58.952
Well, I'm curious.

06:58.986 --> 07:01.388
Mm-hmm.
But I also don't
want to get sick

07:01.421 --> 07:03.123
or have an experience
I'd regret.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.826
I'm just -- I'm not sure
it's worth it.

07:05.859 --> 07:07.561
You're a smart person.

07:07.595 --> 07:10.598
If I were you,
I'd listen to you.

07:12.199 --> 07:13.166
I'm gonna hold off.

07:13.200 --> 07:16.169
I just wanted
to bounce it off of you.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.304
Thanks, dude.

07:20.173 --> 07:21.675
I would like to go
back in time

07:21.709 --> 07:23.811
and have you
raise my kids.
[ Laughs ]

07:23.844 --> 07:25.345
Listen, Brook and I
have our moments,

07:25.378 --> 07:28.148
but we keep it real
'cause we respect each other.

07:28.181 --> 07:30.150
That sounds like my relationship
with my daughter,

07:30.183 --> 07:33.086
except without the respect
or anything I just saw here.

07:33.120 --> 07:34.522
[ Chuckles ]

07:34.555 --> 07:36.857
Can Buddha teach me
how to do that?

07:36.890 --> 07:39.426
Possibly, but you'd have
to invite him over to dinner

07:39.459 --> 07:41.328
to watch the dynamic
between you and your daughter.

07:41.361 --> 07:43.631
Oh, he's dead.
But I can make it.

07:43.664 --> 07:46.199
Okay, that's
a little thirsty...
[ Laughs ]

07:46.233 --> 07:47.935
...but you're cute,

07:47.968 --> 07:49.970
and, uh, you're not
making me read anything,

07:50.003 --> 07:52.105
so dinner tonight?

07:52.139 --> 07:53.373
I'm there.

07:54.474 --> 07:55.643
Oh.

07:55.676 --> 07:58.145
Once my dad finds out
what kind of place you work,

07:58.178 --> 08:00.180
you're gonna hear
some Confucius jokes.

08:00.213 --> 08:03.150
But if you act offended,
he'll double down.

08:07.154 --> 08:09.489
Uh-oh.
Dad's got to the point

08:09.523 --> 08:11.024
where he's gotta label stuff

08:11.058 --> 08:13.126
so he doesn't forget
what it is.

08:13.160 --> 08:16.263
"Snotty child who lives
under my roof."

08:18.899 --> 08:20.534
I'm doing this because
I got a pod

08:20.568 --> 08:22.970
full of Louise's furniture
sitting out on the curb.

08:23.003 --> 08:24.738
I gotta make room for it.

08:24.772 --> 08:26.840
Goodwill's coming by tomorrow
to pick up anything

08:26.874 --> 08:28.408
with a yellow sticker.

08:31.545 --> 08:33.046
[ Laughs ]

08:33.080 --> 08:35.182
Darlene: Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You're not getting rid of that.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.584
I nursed my kids
in that chair.

08:36.617 --> 08:38.185
That was the last time
they were nice to me.

08:38.218 --> 08:39.987
I'm not giving up
that chair.

08:40.020 --> 08:41.188
Okay, I hear you.

08:42.623 --> 08:44.925
Wait a minute.

08:44.958 --> 08:47.160
We've all put our feet
on this coffee table,

08:47.194 --> 08:49.730
and nobody feels guilty
because it's a piece of crap.

08:49.763 --> 08:52.432
I'm not gonna be able to do that
on Louise's coffee table.

08:52.465 --> 08:54.835
And then you know
what's gonna come next?

08:54.868 --> 08:57.270
Coasters.
That's right -- coasters.

08:58.205 --> 09:00.473
All right, fine.

09:02.142 --> 09:04.077
No, not this chair!
Ah!

09:04.111 --> 09:05.879
This is my reading chair!

09:05.913 --> 09:08.115
This is where I escape
to new worlds.

09:08.148 --> 09:11.685
I'll never forget reading
all the Dickens novels

09:11.719 --> 09:14.121
and thinking how lucky
all those kids were

09:14.154 --> 09:16.256
and hoping I could have
what they have one day.

09:18.158 --> 09:20.594
I say lose the chair.
It's gross.

09:20.628 --> 09:23.130
They found hepatitis
on a 5,000-year-old mummy.

09:23.163 --> 09:24.497
You know that chair's
got stuff.

09:26.166 --> 09:29.036
You kids constantly bitch about
how bad your childhoods were,

09:29.069 --> 09:30.704
but you can't bear
to part with anything

09:30.738 --> 09:31.972
that reminds you of 'em.

09:32.005 --> 09:33.106
Well, this is our home.

09:33.140 --> 09:34.474
When I came back
from Chicago,

09:34.507 --> 09:36.076
it was so comforting
to see everything

09:36.109 --> 09:38.111
still the way it was
when I was a kid.

09:38.145 --> 09:40.580
And when I came back to live
here, I felt the same way.

09:40.614 --> 09:42.650
And when I come back in my 40s,
I'm gonna feel the same way.

09:43.651 --> 09:45.653
I always want you guys
to be comfortable,

09:45.686 --> 09:49.156
but I want Louise
to be happy, too.

09:50.691 --> 09:53.894
Anybody here planning
to succeed in the near future

09:53.927 --> 09:54.962
and get a house big enough

09:54.995 --> 09:56.797
to take all this furniture
with them?

09:59.032 --> 10:01.101
Anybody here planning
to succeed?

10:03.370 --> 10:05.138
Anybody here looking forward

10:05.172 --> 10:06.974
to watching Louise
hand me my ass?

10:10.778 --> 10:12.980
So, Nick, I hear you work

10:13.013 --> 10:15.916
at one of those Eastern,
new-agey bookstores.

10:15.949 --> 10:19.086
You know what
Confucius say?
Darlene: Dad, no.

10:19.119 --> 10:20.788
We just
talked about this.

10:20.821 --> 10:22.823
You can't do it at
the Chinese restaurant.

10:22.856 --> 10:23.857
You can't do it here.

10:23.891 --> 10:25.793
You can't do it
anywhere anymore.

10:25.826 --> 10:28.428
I can't keep up!

10:28.461 --> 10:31.198
Just make a list of stuff
that used to be funny

10:31.231 --> 10:32.833
but ain't anymore.

10:32.866 --> 10:35.002
I'd like to get a copy
of that, too.

10:35.035 --> 10:37.304
Oh, you're here.

10:37.337 --> 10:38.638
Grandpa, you called me
and asked me

10:38.672 --> 10:39.973
to come over
and have pizza,

10:40.007 --> 10:42.676
but this is obviously a trick
to get me to talk to her.

10:42.710 --> 10:45.846
No, it was a trick to get you
to come over and talk to me.

10:45.879 --> 10:48.381
Your grandpa misses you.
Oh.

10:48.415 --> 10:50.483
And that was a trick
to get you to stay here

10:50.517 --> 10:51.885
and talk to your mom.

10:51.919 --> 10:53.353
Fine. I'll eat the pizza,
but I'm not interested

10:53.386 --> 10:54.554
in anything she has to say.

10:54.587 --> 10:56.423
It's okay.
No one is.

10:57.725 --> 11:01.028
Continuing that narrative
of disinterest, this is Nick.

11:01.061 --> 11:03.797
He works at that bookstore
I was telling you about.

11:03.831 --> 11:05.999
You must be the kung-fu guy
who tried to teach my mom

11:06.033 --> 11:08.068
a sneaky way to ruin my
relationship with my boyfriend.

11:08.101 --> 11:09.136
Oh, no, no, no.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.371
That was the owner
of the store, River.

11:11.404 --> 11:13.807
What?

11:13.841 --> 11:16.009
The owner of the hippie
bookstore is named River?

11:16.043 --> 11:17.244
Oh, come on, Moonbeam.

11:17.277 --> 11:19.279
You've got to let me
off the leash for this one.

11:20.848 --> 11:22.082
No.

11:22.115 --> 11:23.250
And it doesn't matter
who it was.

11:23.283 --> 11:24.484
I was wrong.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.553
If you mean that,
thank you.

11:26.586 --> 11:28.756
But I can't stay long.
I have to stop at an ATM.

11:28.789 --> 11:30.924
If you need a little cash,
I can help you out.

11:30.958 --> 11:32.259
No, one of Aldo's
kids got sick

11:32.292 --> 11:33.660
and he missed
a few days of work,

11:33.693 --> 11:35.028
so I'm -- I'm helping him
with the rent.

11:36.363 --> 11:37.697
Are you serious?

11:37.731 --> 11:39.066
You're -- You're
watching his kids,

11:39.099 --> 11:40.500
and now you're paying
his rent?

11:40.533 --> 11:42.535
It's a one-time thing.
Don't make a big deal.

11:42.569 --> 11:45.005
Oh, yeah, it's fine,
and when you're at the ATM,

11:45.038 --> 11:46.874
be sure to get some extra
so you can paint his house

11:46.907 --> 11:49.109
and buy him that hoverboard
he's had his eye on.

11:49.142 --> 11:51.111
Why do you always have to be
such a bitch?

11:51.144 --> 11:54.181
[ Gasps ]
Now it's a Conners dinner.

11:54.214 --> 11:56.083
I was just counting down
in my head.

11:57.317 --> 11:58.919
Harris, I have
a daughter your age,

11:58.952 --> 12:01.554
and, um, your mom and I
have been talking about

12:01.588 --> 12:03.023
how you guys are
fighting a lot.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.458
Are you cool
if I weigh in?

12:05.492 --> 12:07.627
Wow, somebody
actually asking me

12:07.660 --> 12:09.096
if they can
butt into my life.

12:09.129 --> 12:10.230
Sure. What the hell.

12:10.263 --> 12:13.733
So, you guys went from,
"How's it going?" to war

12:13.767 --> 12:15.068
in a few seconds.

12:15.102 --> 12:17.104
I think I might have an exercise
that could help you

12:17.137 --> 12:19.372
get a little give and take
in your relationship.

12:19.406 --> 12:20.440
Are you up for that?

12:21.574 --> 12:22.575
Come on.

12:22.609 --> 12:24.077
I mean, what we're doing
isn't working.

12:24.111 --> 12:25.946
I'll give it a shot
if you will.

12:25.979 --> 12:26.980
Fine.

12:29.817 --> 12:31.418
I hope Darlene knows
what she's doing.

12:31.451 --> 12:33.253
Letting a total stranger
get involved

12:33.286 --> 12:35.055
could make this fight
worse.

12:35.088 --> 12:36.790
Oh, I hope not.

12:36.824 --> 12:39.960
But if it does,
I got five bucks on Darlene.

12:39.993 --> 12:42.462
She's way overdue
for a manic phase.

12:42.495 --> 12:43.730
I've fought her.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.165
When she's got
adrenaline going,

12:45.198 --> 12:48.568
she's all teeth
and thumbs to the eyes.

12:48.601 --> 12:51.038
Okay, I want you both
to put your hands up.

12:52.139 --> 12:54.407
Now, I want you
to put your hands

12:54.441 --> 12:57.077
against each other's hands
and push.

12:57.110 --> 13:00.013
This is how your relationship
feels right now.

13:00.047 --> 13:02.149
No movement.
Nobody giving an inch.

13:02.182 --> 13:03.917
In order for things
to change,

13:03.951 --> 13:06.286
you each need to take turns
giving a little.

13:06.319 --> 13:08.688
Okay, so, Harris,
when your mom pushes you

13:08.721 --> 13:10.991
and says she's worried about
Aldo, you give a little.

13:11.024 --> 13:12.993
Darlene,
when Harris pushes back

13:13.026 --> 13:15.628
and says you're interfering
too much, you give a little.

13:15.662 --> 13:18.798
This is how the relationship
stays balanced, okay?

13:18.832 --> 13:20.100
Let's give it a try.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.469
I'm doubling down my bet
on the wiry little vegan.

13:22.502 --> 13:24.204
I'll take that action.

13:24.237 --> 13:25.772
Just watch.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.440
Thumbs and teeth.

13:27.474 --> 13:28.708
Harris:
You heard him, Mom.

13:28.741 --> 13:30.377
I'm an adult
who can date who I want.

13:30.410 --> 13:31.678
Give a little.
No.

13:31.711 --> 13:34.681
Aldo is a 38-year-old loser
who is using you.

13:34.714 --> 13:35.949
You give first.

13:35.983 --> 13:38.018
Oh, so the woman who picks
all the wrong men

13:38.051 --> 13:39.652
wants to tell me
how to pick mine?

13:39.686 --> 13:42.022
Okay, still waiting
for the give and take.

13:42.055 --> 13:44.824
You know, when you make one
smart decision about your life,

13:44.858 --> 13:46.059
you can criticize mine,
okay?

13:46.093 --> 13:47.227
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:47.260 --> 13:49.062
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey.

13:51.064 --> 13:52.900
Why the hell
would you do that?

13:52.933 --> 13:54.334
Because you think
I'm stupid!

13:54.367 --> 13:57.204
You're a sad, pathetic,
miserable person

13:57.237 --> 13:59.039
and you can't stand
that I'm happy.

13:59.072 --> 14:01.174
You're just teaching me
to hate you.

14:01.208 --> 14:02.842
The more time we spend
around each other,

14:02.876 --> 14:04.878
the less we feel like
mother and daughter.

14:04.912 --> 14:07.047
We're just two women
who don't like each other,

14:07.080 --> 14:08.681
so stay away from me.

14:10.918 --> 14:12.185
[ Door slams ]

14:13.420 --> 14:15.588
It usually works
way better than that.

14:19.092 --> 14:21.161
Okay, before I show you
what I did,

14:21.194 --> 14:22.729
the kids were
a little reluctant to part

14:22.762 --> 14:24.097
with some of the furniture,

14:24.131 --> 14:28.335
but I think I blended your stuff
with ours pretty good.

14:28.368 --> 14:32.372
Uh, is that my sofa
on the porch?

14:32.405 --> 14:34.574
Good eye.
Good eye.

14:34.607 --> 14:37.077
I Scotchgarded it so
we could have outdoor living

14:37.110 --> 14:38.912
in the two months
in Chicago

14:38.946 --> 14:40.480
where the weather
won't kill you.

14:42.815 --> 14:44.851
See?

14:44.884 --> 14:46.553
I moved a lot of your stuff
in here.

14:46.586 --> 14:49.122
Uh, hey!
There's your lamp!

14:49.156 --> 14:52.059
And there's
your throw pillows.

14:52.993 --> 14:56.964
Uh, m-my refrigerator's
in front of the closet.

14:56.997 --> 14:58.365
Well,
don't get used to that.

14:58.398 --> 15:01.534
That's only temporary
until I can figure out a way

15:01.568 --> 15:03.470
to get it upstairs
into the hallway.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.572
Be stupid to have two
down here.

15:07.074 --> 15:11.078
Uh, where's my microwave
and my coffeemaker?

15:11.111 --> 15:13.213
Did you get rid of
any of your things?

15:13.246 --> 15:14.647
You weren't here.

15:14.681 --> 15:17.150
Would have been easier
to get rid of the kids.

15:17.184 --> 15:19.552
[ Sighs ]
Look, I tell you what.

15:19.586 --> 15:22.789
The living room and the kitchen
have a long family history

15:22.822 --> 15:25.158
of dysfunction
and petty infighting

15:25.192 --> 15:27.995
and I want
to respect that, so...

15:28.028 --> 15:30.063
I'll put my stuff
in storage

15:30.097 --> 15:33.066
and then you can keep those
rooms exactly as they are.

15:33.100 --> 15:35.135
You're a saint.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.236
Now give me the "but."

15:36.269 --> 15:40.773
But I want the bedroom
to be ours.

15:40.807 --> 15:42.175
And not my bedroom set.

15:42.209 --> 15:45.412
I want a whole new one
so we have a fresh start.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.581
It's the beginning
of our long history together.

15:48.615 --> 15:50.984
[ Smooches ] Done.

15:51.018 --> 15:52.352
Okay, and here's a tip.

15:52.385 --> 15:54.921
When you go
furniture shopping,

15:54.954 --> 15:58.925
pick out exactly what you like
and then ask the salesman,

15:58.958 --> 16:01.494
"What is the complete opposite
of this?"

16:01.528 --> 16:03.163
Then buy that.

16:03.196 --> 16:05.332
Hurtful but fair.

16:09.302 --> 16:10.337
Hey.

16:10.370 --> 16:11.971
Hey, babe.
What are you doing here?

16:12.005 --> 16:13.873
I thought you were
at your mom's tonight.

16:13.906 --> 16:15.808
Ugh, I got into
a huge fight with her,

16:15.842 --> 16:18.045
and I really
don't want to be there.

16:18.078 --> 16:19.612
I know we planned on me
moving in next month,

16:19.646 --> 16:21.348
but can I just
move in now?

16:21.381 --> 16:24.217
I'd love that,
but something came up.

16:25.152 --> 16:28.288
I met with the boys'
school shrink today.

16:28.321 --> 16:30.023
Since you started
spending the night here,

16:30.057 --> 16:33.126
there's been a little
increase in the number
of incidents at school.

16:33.160 --> 16:35.662
W-What kind
of incidents?

16:35.695 --> 16:38.298
It's kind of
an umbrella term for fires,

16:38.331 --> 16:41.068
attacks on teachers,
and throwing a turd in the pool.

16:42.735 --> 16:44.504
I know I may have done that
in the past,

16:44.537 --> 16:47.074
but I-I did not
teach them how.

16:47.107 --> 16:48.007
I-I know.

16:48.041 --> 16:50.077
It's just, she's saying
they're acting out

16:50.110 --> 16:52.812
because they don't want anybody
to replace their mom.

16:52.845 --> 16:55.082
You sleeping here
sends the message,

16:55.115 --> 16:58.185
"We won't get our mom back
while you're still alive."

16:58.218 --> 17:00.087
Holy crap.
They want to kill me?

17:00.120 --> 17:02.755
No.
No, of course not.

17:02.789 --> 17:03.856
So what are you saying?

17:03.890 --> 17:05.825
That I can't
move in here at all?

17:05.858 --> 17:08.928
I-I'm hoping it'll just be
a few months, babe.

17:08.961 --> 17:11.598
Till the kids see
you're not a threat.

17:11.631 --> 17:13.566
Or whenever I can
tweak their meds enough

17:13.600 --> 17:15.935
to get that look
out of their eyes.

17:15.968 --> 17:17.737
This really sucks.

17:17.770 --> 17:20.039
Now my mom has me
right where she wants me.

17:20.073 --> 17:21.374
I'm gonna have to
hide in my room

17:21.408 --> 17:23.110
to avoid listening
to her crap.

17:23.143 --> 17:25.578
Just give her
all good vibes.

17:25.612 --> 17:27.013
And if it gets too bad,

17:27.046 --> 17:29.849
just find a friend
to crash with.

17:29.882 --> 17:32.752
But no strapping dudes
with long, blond hair, okay?

17:35.988 --> 17:37.424
[ Sighs ]

17:37.457 --> 17:39.025
Hey, Moms.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.427
Sorry for blowing up
last night.

17:40.460 --> 17:41.794
All good vibes.
I'm going to my room.

17:41.828 --> 17:43.263
Uh, hold up.

17:43.296 --> 17:44.531
We need to talk.

17:44.564 --> 17:46.065
No, we don't.
We're all good.

17:46.099 --> 17:48.301
Love you like a mother.
Stop.

17:48.335 --> 17:50.137
We're not all good.

17:50.170 --> 17:52.939
I thought about
what you said last night

17:52.972 --> 17:55.608
and it scared me
to death.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.077
You're right.

17:58.111 --> 18:00.079
We're not gonna be
mother and daughter anymore

18:00.113 --> 18:02.582
if we keep ripping
each others' hearts out.

18:05.118 --> 18:07.720
I packed
your suitcases.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.722
[ Voice breaking ]
I think you need to leave now.

18:09.756 --> 18:11.758
You're throwing me out?

18:11.791 --> 18:13.560
If you don't go,

18:13.593 --> 18:16.829
then I'm gonna destroy
our relationship.

18:16.863 --> 18:21.168
I am trying so hard
to learn how to be different,

18:21.201 --> 18:22.569
but I'm afraid
if you stay here

18:22.602 --> 18:24.937
that by the time I do,
it'll be too late

18:24.971 --> 18:26.973
and we're gonna
hate each other.

18:27.006 --> 18:29.108
[ Scoffs ]

18:29.142 --> 18:31.178
Well, thanks for asking me
how I feel.

18:31.211 --> 18:33.146
No, I do know
how you feel.

18:33.180 --> 18:36.349
You want to be with Aldo.
Aldo wants you there.

18:36.383 --> 18:38.151
I think
it's a huge mistake,

18:38.185 --> 18:40.820
but if you're not here,
then we can't fight about it.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.157
Yeah. You're right.

18:44.191 --> 18:46.159
He wants me there,
and you want me gone,

18:46.193 --> 18:47.694
so I'm going.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.028
Hey.

18:51.063 --> 18:52.031
I love you.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.535
Now,
don't be mad at me.

18:55.568 --> 18:57.804
I packed your birth control
in your suitcase,

18:57.837 --> 18:59.339
and I turned on the alarm
on your phone

18:59.372 --> 19:00.607
so you remember
to take them.

19:00.640 --> 19:02.575
I'm sick. I know.
That's why you got to go.

19:09.716 --> 19:11.083
[ Door opens ]

19:29.202 --> 19:34.407
**

19:34.441 --> 19:35.842
Maybe this will help.

19:35.875 --> 19:37.544
It's on me.

19:37.577 --> 19:38.711
Oh, you don't have to.

19:38.745 --> 19:40.313
No, no.
It's store policy.

19:40.347 --> 19:41.648
All relationships
we blow up

19:41.681 --> 19:44.116
get kelp noodles with
hemp seed pesto on the house.

19:45.218 --> 19:47.520
It's okay. You were just trying
to pull up a plane

19:47.554 --> 19:50.156
that's been careening
towards a mountain for 19 years.

19:50.189 --> 19:51.524
You know, you can
tuck your head

19:51.558 --> 19:53.059
between your legs
before a crash,

19:53.092 --> 19:54.961
but you're still gonna end up
stuff on a rock.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.031
So, do you think
I did the right thing?

19:59.065 --> 20:00.166
Yeah, yeah.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.869
I mean, I-I-I think it's great
you were self-aware enough

20:02.902 --> 20:04.937
to take yourself
out of the equation.

20:04.971 --> 20:07.173
This is so damn hard.

20:07.206 --> 20:09.542
Look, we all struggle.

20:09.576 --> 20:11.911
I mean, I told you about
the tough times I had, right?

20:11.944 --> 20:13.713
Yeah, the drugs?
Yeah. Oh, good.

20:13.746 --> 20:15.248
Then I did tell you
about the drugs.

20:15.282 --> 20:16.383
It comes and goes.

20:16.416 --> 20:18.117
I'm Nick, by the way.
[ Chuckles ]

20:19.619 --> 20:21.688
Okay.

20:21.721 --> 20:22.955
Yes.

20:22.989 --> 20:24.424
Yes, what?

20:24.457 --> 20:27.126
Yes, we can date.

20:27.159 --> 20:28.995
That's a little thirsty,
but you're cute.

20:29.962 --> 20:31.631
And you have
such an endearing way

20:31.664 --> 20:34.133
of processing your grief
about your daughter.

20:34.166 --> 20:35.968
And I would be crazy
not to go out with somebody

20:36.002 --> 20:39.138
who left Wall Street to keep
the cucumber water jug full.

20:39.171 --> 20:42.609
Oh, so this relationship's
gonna be based on honesty, huh?

20:42.642 --> 20:46.112
I haven't tried it yet,
but I've heard good things.

20:46.145 --> 20:47.947
I'm glad you feel that way.

20:47.980 --> 20:49.982
And what's the worst
that could happen?

20:50.016 --> 20:52.785
I mean, from what I've
seen of your life, I
can't really ruin it.

20:52.819 --> 20:54.754
Uh, you won't know
until you try.

20:54.787 --> 20:55.955
[ Chuckles ]

20:58.958 --> 21:02.161
Well, I see
you came to your senses

21:02.194 --> 21:04.297
and got rid of that
ridiculous stew train.

21:04.331 --> 21:06.399
The future...

21:06.433 --> 21:08.435
is drones.

21:10.370 --> 21:12.905
One bowl of stew,
coming up.

21:12.939 --> 21:14.807
Oh, no.
Give me a countdown.

21:14.841 --> 21:19.579
Burn victims and lawsuits
in 3, 2, 1...

21:19.612 --> 21:21.013
[ Drone whirring ]

21:22.615 --> 21:24.484
[ Laughing maniacally ]

21:25.785 --> 21:27.620
[ Bowl shatters ]

21:30.122 --> 21:31.524
-- Captions by VITAC --
